element.name: Feeding The Swan's by Windsockers, Traditional Cache (2/1.5)
element.description:
The Cache is situated along the banks of the Broadmeadow Estuary in Swords Co. Dublin,
This is a very popular spot with bird Watchers and also for children to feed the nearby Swan population.
element.long-description:
please take care to rehide the cache as plenty of muggles pass by the location How to Get There:
By bus: Bus 41 from Lower Abbey Street in Dublin city centre to Swords then walk down to the end of North Street in across the footbridge at Estuary Roundabout and continue along the pathway under the Motorway bridge to the rivers edge .
By Car:
Take the exit for Swords on the M1 motorway then take the first exit at The Estuary roundabout and follow the road under the M1 bridge.
About The Estuary:
This Estuary is situated in North Co. Dublin, between the towns of Swords,Malahide & Donabate.
This is the estuary of the River Broadmeadow, a substantial river which drains the local agricultural area, there is also a railway viaduct, built in the 1800s that devides the estuary and has led to the inner estuary becoming lagoonal in character and only partly tidal. It is also possible to continue around the estuary and along the north shore all the way to Donabate where The Newbridge Demense cache can also be found,
(if you wish to do this please take note of the tidal times as some parts of the roadways are under water at high tide as seen in the photo)
The Windsockers

2010-06-14T19:00:00Z : Didn't find it by RoobyDoo
Had a good look for this one. Found the perfect spot for a cache in line with the clue, but no cache. Searched for some time before giving up. Thanks for a great walk though. RD

2010-05-15T19:00:00Z : Found it by Alastair74
Found while spending the day in Dublin for the WWFM with Wildfowler TFTC

2010-05-15T19:00:00Z : Found it by wildfowler
Found on a caching weekend around Dublin with Alastair74! TNLNSL TFTC

2010-05-08T19:00:00Z : Didn't find it by abra123cadabra
We thought we found the place in the hint but couldn't spot the container. We'll have another look next time. With under one hour to low tide the road is still flooded. Amazing how brave people are... maybe they are locals. We even saw cyclists driving through the water.

2010-04-23T19:00:00Z : Found it by Sookmeister
Took me a while but found it with Carlymonster eventually. Nice hide.
TFTC

2008-09-27T19:00:00Z : Found it by Kersti.com
So many swans! And they didn't really seem particularly bothered by the car. We managed to get through eventually and made our way to the cache. We re-thought our initial ideas of where it could be and soon had the cache in hand.
